p:::s6:::Tom falls in love with Becky Thatcher , a new girl in town , and persuades her to get `` engaged '' to him .
n:::s7:::Their romance collapses when she learns that Tom has been `` engaged '' before -- to a girl named Amy Lawrence .
n:::s8:::Shortly after being shunned by Becky , Tom accompanies Huckleberry Finn , the son of the town drunk , to the graveyard at night to try out a `` cure '' for warts .
p:::s19:::Back in school , Tom gets himself back in Becky 's favor after he nobly accepts the blame for a book that she has ripped .
p:::s30:::Meanwhile , Tom goes on a picnic to McDougal 's Cave with Becky and their classmates .
p:::s34:::Tom and Becky get lost in the cave , and their absence is not discovered until the following morning .
p:::s36:::Tom and Becky run out of food and candles and begin to weaken .
